      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, it definitely feels more natural than a bot. But I'm worried that if the sentiment classifier is really sensitive to words like \"issues\" or \"smaller\" or \"quibbles,\" it might still flag the review as mediocre or negative. \n\nCan we try a version where you lean a bit more into the positive descriptions? I still want people to know the service was slow and the rooms were tight, but maybe you can frame those things in a way that keeps the overall vibe super upbeat so the score stays in the high range? Like, instead of \"issues,\" maybe phrase it as a \"slower, more relaxed pace\"? Just try to make it sound even more glowing while still being technically true.",
